That's the lesson radio station Hot 97 learned after morning host Peter Rosenberg spoke disparagingly about Minaj's song 'Starships.' The rap superstar was supposed to headline Hot 97's Summer Jam concert at MetLife Stadium but was pulled from hip-hop's biggest concert just hours before she was slated to perform because the Hot 97 on-air personality dissed her — angering the head of her record label, Lil’ Wayne, who then axed her performance.
